title: tensorflow.python.framework.errors_impl.NotFoundError: /home/robot/learning_to_sample/classification/structural_losses/tf_nndistance_so.so: undefined symbol: _ZTIN10tensorflow8OpKernelE
body:
After I trained Pointnet ang got the classification model, I run "python train_SNET.py --classifier_model_path log/baseline/PointNet1024/model.ckpt --num_out_points 64 --log_dir log/SNET64" and got error "nn_distance_so.so" not found.
 So I checked the folder "structural_losses" just to find there is no file named "nn_distance_so.so" indeed. 
Then I run "make" in terminal to execute makefile, and got error "nsync.h not found" .So I followed the instructions on a web page, downloading .h files in https://github.com/google/nsync/tree/master/public this website to usr/include. 
And the file nn_distance_so.so is created successfully.
However, when I run "python train_SNET.py --classifier_model_path log/baseline/PointNet1024/model.ckpt --num_out_points 64 --log_dir log/SNET64" again, I got the error  _ZTIN10tensorflow8OpKernelE as the title describes.
I don't know how to fix it.
Can anybody help?
(use python 2.7 and gcc 5.4.0)


robot@robot-OMEN-by-HP-Obelisk-Desktop-875-1xxx:~/learning_to_sample/classification$ python train_SNET.py --classifier_model_path log/PointNet1024/model.ckpt --num_out_points 64 --log_dir log/SNET64
